                "subtree_end_index": 270,
                "nodes": []
              },
              {
                "title": "10.1 Cleaning validation should be performed in order to confirm the effectiveness of any cleaning procedure for all product contact equipment. Simulating agents may",
                "node_id": "0317",
                "start_index": 270,
                "end_index": 270,
                "own_start_index": 270,
                "own_end_index": 270,
                "subtree_start_index": 270,
                "subtree_end_index": 270,
                "nodes": []
              },
              {
                "title": "10.2 A visual check for cleanliness is an important part of the acceptance criteria for cleaning validation. It is not generally acceptable for this criterion alone to be used. Repeated cleaning and retesting until acceptable residue results",
                "node_id": "0318",
                "start_index": 270,
                "end_index": 270,
                "own_start_index": 270,
                "own_end_index": 270,
                "subtree_start_index": 270,
                "subtree_end_index": 270,
                "nodes": []
              },
              {
                "title": "10.3 It is recognised that a cleaning validation programme may take some time to complete and validation with verification after each batch may be required for some products e.g. investigational medicinal products. There should be sufficient data from the…",
                "node_id": "0319",
                "start_index": 270,
                "end_index": 270,
                "own_start_index": 270,
                "own_end_index": 270,
                "subtree_start_index": 270,
                "subtree_end_index": 270,
                "nodes": []
              },
              {
                "title": "10.4 Validation should consider the level of automation in the cleaning process. Where an automatic process is used, the specified normal operating range of the utilities and equipment should be validated.",
                "node_id": "0320",
                "start_index": 270,
                "end_index": 270,
                "own_start_index": 270,
                "own_end_index": 270,
                "subtree_start_index": 270,
                "subtree_end_index": 270,
                "nodes": []
              },
              {
                "title": "10.5 For all cleaning processes an assessment should be performed to determine the variable factors which influence cleaning effectiveness and performance, e.g. operators, the level of detail in procedures such as rinsing times etc. If variable factors have…",
                "node_id": "0321",
                "start_index": 270,
                "end_index": 270,
                "own_start_index": 270,
                "own_end_index": 270,
                "subtree_start_index": 270,
                "subtree_end_index": 270,
                "nodes": []
              },
              {
                "title": "10.6 Limits for the carryover of product residues should be based on a toxicological evaluation. The justification for the selected limits should be documented in a risk assessment which includes all the supporting references. Limits should be established for…",
                "node_id": "0322",
                "start_index": 270,
                "end_index": 270,
                "own_start_index": 270,
                "own_end_index": 270,
                "subtree_start_index": 270,
                "subtree_end_index": 270,
                "nodes": []
              },
              {
                "title": "10.6.1 Therapeutic macromolecules and peptides are known to degrade and denature when exposed to pH extremes and/or heat, and may become pharmacologically inactive. A",
                "node_id": "0323",
                "start_index": 270,
